ğŸ› ï¸ 5. Step-by-Step Build Manual
Step 1 â€” Mount the Lid Servo

Attach the servo near the hinge

Use a servo horn to push/lift the lid

Test angles using simple servo sweep code first

Tighten screws so the servo does not wobble

Step 2 â€” Install the Top Ultrasonic Sensor

Mount inside the lid

Must face straight down

Measure distance from sensor to bin floor â†’ update BIN_HEIGHT_CM

Step 3 â€” Install the Front Ultrasonic Sensor

Mount on the bin front

Height: around your hand level

Angle: facing outward, not downward

Step 4 â€” Mount LCD

Use screws or glue

Orient so text is readable at standing height

Step 5 â€” Install LEDs

Drill small holes for LEDs

Or mount them on the lid panel

Ensure resistors are in series

Step 6 â€” Install Buzzer

Mount near a ventilation hole

Must not be blocked to keep sound loud

Step 7 â€” Wire Everything

Follow the wiring table & diagrams

Keep ground wires common

Zip-tie wires to avoid tangling

Step 8 â€” Upload Code

Paste the full code you already have

Install LiquidCrystal_I2C library

Set correct LCD address (0x27 or 0x3F)

ğŸ§ª 6. Testing Checklist
âœ” Sensor Testing

Move hand in front â†’ distance should decrease

Add object inside bin â†’ top sensor should measure correctly

âœ” Servo Testing

Hand must stay for required time (800ms default)

Servo opens smoothly

Closes after 3 seconds

âœ” Level Detection

Add trash gradually

Check LCD percentage updates correctly

âœ” Buzzer Test

Simulate full bin by covering top sensor

Buzzer should beep repeatedly

âœ” LED Tests

Green LED (<80%)

Yellow LED (80â€“99%)

Red LED (100%)

Lid LED on only when lid is open

